
$ Validation: Simply supported beam — mid-span point load (SOL 101)
$ Euler-Bernoulli closed-form: delta_mid = P*L^3 / (48*E*I)
$
$ Geometry:  L = 10 m, 10 equal CBAR elements (1 m each), 11 nodes
$            Node 6 (x = 5 m) is at mid-span
$ Material:  Steel — E = 200 GPa, nu = 0.3, rho = 7850 kg/m^3
$ Section:   Solid square, side = 0.31623 m
$              A  = 0.1 m^2
$              I1 = I2 = a^4/12 = 8.333e-4 m^4
$ Load:      P = 1000 N in -Z at mid-span (node 6)
$ BCs:       Node 1 (x=0): pin — Tx Ty Tz Rx Rz fixed, Ry free
$            Node 11 (x=10): roller — Tz fixed, Ry free
$            (Ty Rx Rz also fixed at node 11 to prevent out-of-plane RBMs)
$
$ Expected:  delta_mid = 1000 * 10^3 / (48 * 2e11 * 8.333e-4) = 1.250e-4 m (0.125 mm, -Z)
$ Units:     SI (m, N, kg, Pa)
$
SOL 101
$
SUBCASE 1
  TITLE        = Simply Supported Mid-Span Load — Validation
  SPC          = 1
  LOAD         = 10
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  SPCFORCE     = ALL
  FORCE        = ALL
  STRESS       = ALL
$
